<item>
            <title>[TIKA-219] Split Tika to separate modules</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-219</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed recently on the mailing list &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, it would be good to split Tika to components based on use cases and external dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed split is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;tika-core - core parts of Tika; everything but cli, gui, and the parser.* packages&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;tika-parsers - format-specific parser classes; with dependencies to external libraries&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;tika-app - depends on all of the above; adds cli and gui; standalone jar packaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/tavirkqhn6r2szrz&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/tavirkqhn6r2szrz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
